NERON

Because Eleesha was designed with skills for mush hunting and therefore this is what she is expected of in the metagame. A lot of players are not confident in their hunting skills so they avoid the character that is expected to be a hunter. [6826491]

A reminder for everyone: Please don't discourage people from jumping.

You might think your ship is bad...and objectively, it might be. The right people jumping onto it could turn a bad situation around. Some of the best stories come about from a ship that by all rights, could have ended in abject failure, and the crew rallied to turn the tables on that fate. I've had many of those, and I'm not the only one here who can say so.

If you discourage people from jumping, just because YOU have given up, that bitterness will carry over to other ships, and it ultimately hurts the community. It does NOT mean that other players will give up so easily, nor should they. Few people will remember a ship where everyone simply gave up. Apathy and excessive negativity are even worse.

Sometimes you have to roll the hard six. Play it out to the end, even if it's a bitter end. Learn from it, and be a better player for it.

On august 16, 2018
Chime

Not really in that case he'd definitely land on a different ship.

You basically compare your selection with the remaining characters missing on the ship you are trying to jump on. If the selection fits and only characters that aren't already awake are shown you jump and if you are lucky you end up on the ship you wanted. If there's a character in your selection that is already awake on the ship you want to jump on you'll definitely land on a different ship.
